      "review_verdict": "DISPUTED_FP",
      "original_classification": "vulnerability",
      "adjusted_severity": "Informational",
      "reviewer_notes": "Gate 5 (Spec Cross-Reference) triggered. The 01e property (from outputs/01e_PARTIAL_MANUAL_kzg_infinity.json) states 'KZG commitment validation must reject the point at infinity as an invalid commitment.' However, official Ethereum consensus-spec-tests include test vectors that EXPECT identity point commitments to be accepted for zero data (verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_case_valid_multiple_blobs_9a17d94b4a0da274: output=true with 0xc000...0000 commitment and all-zero cells). Mathematically, a zero polynomial correctly produces an identity commitment (confirmed by test_commit_g1_identity_when_poly_is_zero at target_workspace/crates/cryptography/kzg_multi_open/src/commit_key.rs:107-116). The code's acceptance of identity points via blstrs::G1Point::from_compressed is spec-compliant, not a vulnerability. The 01e property contradicts official test vectors.",
      "spec_reference": "KZG commitment validation must reject the point at infinity (identity element of the elliptic curve group) as an invalid commitment. A commitment equal to the identity point does not correspond to any valid polynomial and must not pass verification. (01e_PARTIAL_MANUAL_kzg_infinity.json)"
    }
